## Summary of Changes

### Problem
The application was migrated from PatternFly 5 to PatternFly 6, but the build was failing due to incompatible dependency versions and residual PF5 code patterns.

### Fixes Applied

#### 1. Dependency Upgrades (`package.json`)

| Package | Before | After | Reason |
|---|---|---|---|
| `@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk-webpack` | `^1.2.0` | `^4.21.0` | Old version incompatible with React 18 / PF6 |
| `@patternfly/react-topology` | `^5.4.0` | `^6.4.0` | Still on PF5, needed PF6 |
| `typescript` | `^4.7.4` | `^5.7.2` | Required by the updated SDK webpack plugin |

Added `webpack: "5.75.0"` to `resolutions` to prevent the SDK webpack plugin from using its own nested webpack 5.107.2, which caused `ModuleFederationPlugin` hook incompatibilities.

#### 2. Webpack Config (`webpack.config.ts`)
- Added `validateSharedModules: false` to `ConsoleRemotePlugin()` — the SDK 4.21.0 still lists `react: ^17.0.1` in its dependencies, but PF6 requires React 18. This validation would be resolved when the Console itself upgrades to React 18.

#### 3. Source Code Fixes

- **`src/components/DropdownWithKebab.tsx`**: Moved `Modal`, `ModalBody`, `ModalFooter`, `ModalHeader` imports from `@patternfly/react-core/next` (PF5 "next" subpath, empty in PF6) to `@patternfly/react-core` (where they live in PF6).

- **`src/components/KuadrantOverviewPage.tsx`**: Changed `class` to `className` on `<DropdownList>` (line 830).

#### 4. Tests
No unit/integration test suite exists in this project. The `test-frontend.sh` script only validates i18n file freshness.
